        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>You Must Be Alive To Vote Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill requires each state, in order to receive certain education and transportation funds, to annually certify that the state has an agreement with the Social Security Administration to share death information for the purpose of removing the names of ineligible voters from the official list of eligible voters.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
